Name: Siberian Husky
Description: The Siberian Husky is a medium-sized working dog breed originally bred by the Chukchi people of Siberia to pull sleds over long distances. They are known for their endurance, striking blue or multicolored eyes, and thick double coat. Huskies are energetic, friendly, and require regular exercise and mental stimulation.

Name: Bernese Mountain Dog
Description: The Bernese Mountain Dog is a large, sturdy breed from the Swiss Alps, historically used as a farm dog for herding cattle and pulling carts. They are known for their tri-colored coat, calm temperament, and devotion to their families. Bernese Mountain Dogs thrive in active households and enjoy cold climates.

Name: Maine Coon
Description: The Maine Coon is one of the largest domestic cat breeds, originating in the northeastern United States. They have long, shaggy fur, tufted ears, and bushy tails designed for cold climates. Maine Coons are gentle, sociable, and often described as 'dog-like' due to their playful loyalty and friendliness.

Name: British Shorthair
Description: The British Shorthair is a stocky, medium-to-large cat breed from the United Kingdom, best known for its round face, dense coat, and calm personality. They are affectionate but not overly demanding, making them ideal for families. Their plush 'teddy bear' appearance and quiet demeanor make them one of the most popular cat breeds worldwide.

Name: Mixed / Unknown Dog
Description: Many shelter dogs are mixed breeds with uncertain ancestry. Mixed-breed dogs often combine the traits of multiple breeds, making them unique in appearance and temperament. They are known for their resilience, adaptability, and can be excellent family companions.

Name: Mixed / Unknown Cat
Description: Most shelter cats are domestic short-haired or long-haired mixes with no specific breed lineage. These cats vary in size, coat length, and personality, offering a wide range of wonderful companions for adopters.
